						density and unit type closest to that of the proposed project.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(g) This section shall be applicable to charter cities because the Legislature finds that the lack of housing, including emergency shelter, is a critical statewide problem.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(h) The following definitions apply for the purposes of this section:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) “Feasible” means capable of being accomplished in a successful manner within a reasonable period of time, taking into account economic, environmental, social, and technological factors.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) “Housing development project” means a use consisting of any of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Residential units
