						Section 10000), of Division 2 of Title 1 of the Corporations Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(11) “Title V industrial use” means a use that is a Title V source, as defined in Section 39053.5 of the Health and Safety Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(12) “Use by right” means a development project that satisfies both of the following conditions:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The development project does not require a conditional use permit, planned unit development permit, or other discretionary local government review.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The development project is not a “project” for purposes of Division 13 (commencing with Section 21000) of the Public Resources Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) Notwithstanding
