						violations or complaints alleging building code violations.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s310.969736391837776"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 31.</h3> Section 17958.7 of the Health and Safety Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_E21105FF-389C-475B-BF98-90AD6A3C5DD7"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">17958.7.</h6> (a) Except as provided in subdivision (c) and in Section 17922.6, the governing body of a city or county, before making any modifications or changes pursuant to Section 17958.5, shall make an express finding that such modifications or changes are reasonably necessary because of local climatic, geological, or topographical conditions. Such a finding shall be available as a public record. A copy of those findings, together with the modification or change expressly marked and identified to which each finding refers, shall be filed with the California Building Standards Commission. No modification or change shall become effective or operative for any purpose until the finding and the modification or change have been filed with the California Building
